  <thing id="sDN6001" name="Acid Fog" description="{i}Acid fog{/i} creates a billowing mass of misty vapors similar to that produced by a {i}solid fog{/i} spell (PH 281) {b} in an area of 20 ft. radius, 20 ft. high{/b}. In addition to slowing creatures down and obscuring sight, this spell&#146;s vapors are highly acidic. Each round on your turn, starting when you cast the spell, the fog deals 2d6 points of acid damage to each creature and object within it.\n\n{i}Arcane Material Component{/i}: A pinch of dried, powdered peas combined with powdered animal hoof." compset="Spell" summary="Fog deals acid damage.">
