  <thing id="cDeathDelv" name="Death Delver" description="{b}Special Entry Requirement{/b}: Must have had at least one near-death experience (fallen below 0 hit points and lived)\n\n{i}&#147;Many have gazed into the abyss, but how many have the strength to meet its stare when it gazes back at them?&#148;{/i}\n                        &#151;Fortenus, Death Delver\n\nThe mystery of death and dying is one that occupies the attention of almost every race, regardless of that race&#146;s behaviors or beliefs. The death delver is that rare individual who, rather than fearing and avoiding death, delves as deeply into its mysteries as he can, to better understand and eventually gain some small power over it. Unlike necromancers and other classes associated with death magic,  the focus of a death delver&#146;s studies&#151;or, more accurately, his journey&#151;is much more deeply personal. Rather than concentrating on using death and death magic to affect the outside world, a death delver seeks to attune himself to the ebb and flow of death itself, and thereby draw strength from his understanding and indomitable courage in the face of it.\n\n{b}BECOMING A DEATH DELVER{/b}\nUnlike many prestige classes, the death delver is open and appealing to characters of any prior class; the only common thread is that the individual possess a refl ective disposition and a keen interest in death. The death delver&#146;s meditative nature perhaps makes it most appealing to priests, monks, and other philosophically minded individuals, but any character with a genuine passion for the exploration of death and dying is a good candidate for the class. Wisdom (for spells), Constitution (for facing death without fear), and Charisma (for several class features) are key abilities for death delvers.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Heroes of Horror" compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="10">
    <usesource source="HeroHorror"/>
    <tag group="ClassType" tag="Prestige"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cHelpDeD"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="helper" thing="cHelpDeD"/>
    <exprreq message="Concentration 8 ranks required"><![CDATA[#skillranks[kConcent] >= 8]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Heal 2 ranks required"><![CDATA[#skillranks[kHeal] >= 2]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Knowledge (Religion) 4 ranks required"><![CDATA[#skillranks[kKnowRel] >= 4]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base Will Save +2 required"><![CDATA[child[vWill].field[vBase].value >= 2]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDDeathSe" name="Deathsense" description="You have the infallible ability to detect the presence and condition of nearby life. This ability functions as the spell {i}deathwatch{/i} (see page 217 of the {i}Player&#146;s Handbook{/i}) but can be invoked at will, with no cost, as a swift action." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Sense the presence and condition of nearby life.">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Sense"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDRebukeU" name="Rebuke Undead" description="Like an evil cleric, you can rebuke undead. Use your death delver level as the cleric level for determining success and damage. You can do this a number of times per day equal to 3 + your Charisma modifier and can take the Extra Turning feat to gain additional turn attempts. If you already have the ability to rebuke undead from a previous class, death delver levels stack with those class levels for the purposes of rebuking undead." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Rebuke undead as an evil cleric.">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xTurning"></bootstrap>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="12000" index="2">~ Modify livename and summary
  hero.child[xTurning].field[livename].text = field[name].text
  hero.child[xTurning].field[xSumm].text = field[summary].text
  perform hero.child[xTurning].assign[Turning.Rebuke]</eval>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="10000"><![CDATA[~ If we're not shown, just get out now
  doneif (tagis[Helper.ShowSpec] = 0)

~ Add our level to our turning level.
  hero.child[xTurning].field[Value].value += field[xTotalLev].value]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDDeadSou" name="Deadened Soul" description="Upon reaching 2nd level, your understanding of death has progressed to the point where you no longer fear it, nor anything else. You are immune to fear effects of any kind." compset="ClSpecial" summary="You are immune to fear effects of any kind.">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Immune"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <bootstrap thing="xImmFear">
      <containerreq phase="First" priority="10000"><![CDATA[count:Classes.DeathDelv >= 2]]></containerreq>
      </bootstrap>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDSpoCast" name="Spontaneous Casting" description="By 2nd level, your familiarity with the ebb and flow of death has blossomed to the point that, like a cleric, you can lose any prepared spell in order to cast any {i}cure{/i} spell of the same level or lower. An evil death delver can only spontaneously convert prepared spells into {i}inflict{/i} spells of equal level or lower. Neutral death delvers must choose whether they will cast spontaneous {i}cure{/i} or {i}inflict{/i} spells and can never change their selection once the choice has been made." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Lose any prepared spell to cast {i}cure{/i} or {i}inflict{/i} spells.">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="2"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Immune"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDDeaWard" name="Death Ward" description="At 3rd level, you gain the ability to mystically protect yourself or another from the depredations of death magic and life-draining attacks. This supernatural ability functions exactly like the spell {i}death ward{/i} (see page 217 of the {i}Player&#146;s Handbook{/i}), save that the duration is 1 hour per death delver level. Using this ability is a standard action.\n\nYou gain an additional use of this ability per day upon reaching 6th level, and again at 9th level." compset="ClSpecial" summary="You can mystically protect yourself or another from death magic.">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="3"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Defense"/>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="10000"><![CDATA[if (#levelcount[DeathDelv] >= 9) then
 field[hTotal].value = 3
elseif (#levelcount[DeathDelv] >= 6) then
 field[hTotal].value = 2
else
 field[hTotal].value = 1
endif]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDDiehard" name="Diehard" description="Death delvers of at least 4th level gain the benefit of the Diehard feat (see page 93 of the {i}Player&#146;s Handbook{/i}), even if they do not meet the prerequisites." compset="ClSpecial" summary="You can mystically protect yourself or another from death magic.">
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="3"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <tag group="SpecType" tag="Defense"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="SpecUp"/>
    <bootstrap thing="fDiehard">
      <containerreq phase="First" priority="10000"><![CDATA[count:Classes.DeathDelv >= 3]]></containerreq>
      <autotag group="thing" tag="skipprereq"/>
      </bootstrap>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDFearAur" name="Fear Aura" description="Starting at 5th level, once per day you can emanate a nearly palpable aura of fear in a 30-foot radius. The effect lasts for a number of rounds equal to your class level. Enemies (not allies) within the area must make a Will save (DC 10 + class level + your Cha modifier) or be affected as if by a {i}fear{/i} spell (see page 229 of the {i}Player&#146;s Handbook{/i})." compset="ClSpecial" summary="30-foot radius aura of fear causes enemies to be shaken">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="5"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <eval phase="PostAttr" priority="12000" index="2"><![CDATA[var DC as number

DC = 10 + #levelcount[DeathDelv] + hero.child[aCHA].field[aModBonus].value

field[xSumm].text = field[summary].text & " (DC " & DC & ")."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDCheatDe" name="Cheat Death" description="Upon reaching 7th level, your mastery over death and dying has progressed to the point where you can deny a foe the ability to send you into death&#146;s embrace in a single, cowardly blow. Whenever anyone attempts a coup de grace on you, you automatically make the subsequent Fortitude save (see pages 153&#150;154 of the Player&#146;s Handbook). The attacker still deals just as much damage as she normally would, and you could still die from that damage. Similarly, when you take massive damage (50 or more points of damage from a single attack), you automatically succeed on the Fortitude save to survive the associated trauma (see page 145 of the Player&#146;s Handbook), although you can be killed by sheer damage dealt." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Automatically save against coup de grace and massive damage.">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="7"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDManLife" name="Mantle of Life" description="Beginning at 8th level, you gain the ability to project your own wisdom and confidence into your allies. As a full-round action, you can send a surge of vitality through all companions within 60 feet. This surge grants every ally in the area (including yourself) a +4 bonus on Will saves for 1 minute per class level." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Grant allies within 60&apos; a +4 bonus on Will Saves">
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="8"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Super"/>
    <eval phase="PostLevel" priority="12000"><![CDATA[var lvl as number
lvl = #levelcount[DeathDelv]
field[xSumm].text = field[summary].text & " for " & lvl & " minutes."]]></eval>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cDDNineLiv" name="Nine Lives" description="The pinnacle of achievement for a death delver is the remarkable ability to step back through death&#146;s door when forcibly pushed through it. Upon reaching 10th level, you gain the ability to cheat death nine times&#151;in effect, gaining nine bonus lives. Every time a single attack, spell, or effect would drop you below &#150;10 hit points or otherwise kill you, you lose one of your nine lives in lieu of taking the effects of whatever would have killed you; instead you drop to &#150;9 hit points but are stable. Continuing sources of damage, such as being dropped into lava or held under water, will of course burn through a character&#146;s nine lives in no time. Keep track of how many lives you&#146;ve used, because once they&#146;re gone, they&#146;re gone.\n\nFor example, consider a death delver with seven lives and 11 hit points remaining who is struck by a critical hit that deals 32 points of damage. Since dropping to &#150;21 hit points would kill him, he automatically loses one of his remaining bonus lives instead and stabilizes at &#150;9 hit points, leaving him with six lives remaining. Later in the adventure, after he has been fully healed, a dread witch hits him with a {i}disintegrate{/i} spell, which would normally reduce him to a pile of dust. He is once again reduced to &#150;9 hit points and marks off another life (leaving fi ve bonus lives remaining). He&#146;s not having a very good week, but at least he&#146;s still around to complain about it." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Avoid certain death up to 9 times.">
    <fieldval field="hTotal" value="9"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="10"/>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowCharge"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpDeD"/>
    </thing>
  <thing id="sDDBless" name="Bless" description="{i}Bless{/i} fills your allies {b}(all allies within a 50-ft. burst, centered on the caster){/b} with courage. Each ally gains a +1 morale bonus on attack rolls and on saving throws against fear effects.\n\n{i}Bless{/i} counters and dispels {i}bane{/i}." compset="Spell" summary="Allies gain +1 on attack rolls and +1 on saves against fear.">
